### About Hamilton AI

We are on a mission to build the premier operating system for private aviation. Beginning with a comprehensive productivity suite tailored for private aviation charter brokers and operators, we are transforming how charters are sourced, trips are managed, payments are processed, and trip progress is tracked. Despite being a market valued at over $30 billion annually, private charter operations are currently run with technology that lags two decades behind. Hamilton AI is set to change that by leveraging cutting-edge technology and user-centered design.

### What You'll Be Working On

- Enhancing our artificial intelligence assistant's user interface, ensuring seamless interaction across the application, including the marketplace, trip management, payments, and more.
- Leading the development and refinement of our web application's front-end, focusing on trip management and streamlined request generation.
- Collaborating closely with backend developers to integrate real-time global aircraft availability and live airplane transponder data into our user-facing features.
- Utilizing advanced machine learning insights to inform UI/UX decisions, particularly for features forecasting pricing and market depth by route and aircraft type.
- Implementing and improving payment solution integrations within the application to offer a frictionless user payment experience.
- Incorporating AI-driven suggestions into the application's UI to enhance user experience across our technology stack.

### What We're Looking For

- Hamilton AI is assembling its initial technology team, comprising four engineers specialized in backend, frontend, full-stack development, and one UX/UI engineer, with a current focus on expanding our front-end development capabilities.
- We are seeking a Front-End Engineer who is enthusiastic about startups and eager to contribute to the foundational engineering team.
- Ideal candidates will have a robust portfolio demonstrating proficiency in front-end development, with a deep understanding of user experience design, performance optimization, and cross-platform development.
- Expertise in modern front-end technologies and frameworks, particularly ReactJS, is essential.
- A passion for developing intuitive, responsive, and visually appealing web applications.
- The ability to work closely with UX/UI designers and translate design concepts into functional and dynamic user interfaces.
- Excellent communication skills to effectively collaborate with team members across different disciplines.

### Minimum Requirements

- A degree in computer science or a related field.
- 2-4 years of relevant experience in front-end development.
- Profound understanding of front-end technologies, including HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript/ES6.
- Extensive experience with ReactJS or similar modern front-end frameworks (e.g., Vue.js, Angular).
- Experience with responsive and adaptive design principles.

### Additional Pluses

- 4-6+ years of relevant work experience in front-end development.
- Experience leading or mentoring junior front-end developers.
- Experience in working closely with the product side of a business to translate business requirements into technical solutions.
- Knowledge of web performance optimization techniques.
- Familiarity with front-end testing frameworks and methodologies.
- Experience with additional front-end technologies such as TypeScript, Sass/Less, Webpack, and Babel.
- Experience integrating with RESTful APIs and understanding of backend technologies.

highlightedJobListings.description:
Semiconductor chips are the driving force behind the modern technology-driven world. They power everything from cars to rockets, sensors to servers, and have a crucial role to play in several major industries, making the $1T semiconductor industry a vital component of the global economy. However, designing modern semiconductor chips is a costly, engineering-intensive process, further worsened with archaic tools. With the rising complexity of chips, time and cost to market continues to rise.

To address this, we're reimagining how chips are designed using modern advancements in AI to reduce time/cost to market dramatically. With a growing number of organizations designing their own chips and the rising consumption of semiconductors in day-to-day life, the work you will do will significantly impact the lives of many. We are super excited about what we are building; come join us!

**What are we looking for?**
We are looking for an exceptional Applied Research Engineer to join our founding team and contribute to improving our in-house large language models (LLMs). In this role, you will apply cutting-edge techniques to fine-tune LLMs and implement novel ways to improve their performance on our target applications.

This is a unique opportunity to work at the forefront of LLMs while surrounded by exceptional researchers and builders at AI2. As a founding member of a rapidly growing startup, you will significantly impact the product and shape its future. We offer competitive pay, benefits, and equity, and believe this position will be fulfilling for you.

**Ideal Candidate**
Several years of full-time experience in applied ML roles, preferably in a fast-paced environment like early-stage startups.

**Non-negotiable**

* Deep passion for technology. Self-driven individual with a sense of urgency
* Detail oriented and a strong desire to build high-quality customer-focused products

**Requirements**

* Strong basics and understanding of Machine Learning/Deep Learning
* Experience in building diverse and high-quality datasets and training deep learning models
* Strong programming skills in Python
* Familiarity with deep learning frameworks such as TensorFlow or PyTorch
* Exposure to or active participation in the latest research and advancements in NLP

**Preferences**

Experience in code generation with LLMs
Prior experience in fine-tuning large language models desirable
Experience setting up infrastructure for training large deep-learning models

**Not Necessary**

Experience in chip design great but NOT necessary

**ABOUT US**

We are a small but passionate group with a mission to dramatically reduce the time, cost, and engineering effort needed to build complex silicon chips. Our founding team comprises of experts in chip design, AI, and modern software stacks. In past lives—we were researchers, engineers, and leaders at major chip design/AI companies like Qualcomm, Nvidia, Facebook, Google, etc. We also count the Paul Allen Institute for AI as a co-founder, one of the world’s leading A.I. research institutions. We recently raised a pre-seed funding round and are moving fast to build for our customers.

**WHY JOIN**

As a funded startup, we also have several unique benefits that you can’t really get anywhere else:

Personal impact — The opportunity to build something from the ground up and define a new product for an industry that is at the core of the modern technological revolution.
Access to unique learning opportunities — With the Allen Institute for AI (AI2) as a co-founder, our team gets access to numerous talks by leading AI researchers/paper authors, knowledge sharing amongst the community of hundreds of engineers working for AI2 companies, and much more. As a part of the multi-disciplinary team, you get to interact with people from very different backgrounds (from chip design to AI to software engineers).
Founding title — You will be one of our first hires. For the rest of our days, no matter how many thousands of people join after you, you will always have that honor and distinction.
Early-stage equity — Early-stage risk comes with early-stage equity for you. And none of us would be here if we didn’t think our company would create tremendous value over time.
Benefits — In spite of being an early-stage company, taking care of our team is a priority for us. From health insurance to catered lunches, we continue to add unique benefits.

As a engineer at Bask you will work directly with the CEO and CTO to build and design the software infrastructure that will serve as the backbone of telehealth.

We are looking to expand our software engineers, seeking those with deep rooted entrepreneurial spirit.

Our serverless platform is built using Next.js, Drizzle and PlanetScale for a powerful multi-tenant application.

It is important to be fluent in these frameworks, with Javascript and API architecture being a must.

What You'll Do

• Design, build, and implement new services through the full development cycle: write elegant, well-tested code in a modern technology stack. Build libraries and frameworks that can help us build quickly and efficiently, and deliver value to our users.

• Work closely with the product team: make architecture and design decisions, participate in stand-ups, code reviews, and retros, and help contribute and drive the engineering culture that focuses on simple, intuitive, high-impact experiences.

• Be an engineering generalist: from developing servers and databases, to integrating APIs to expand our platforms capabilities, to final Ul implementation, to you'll have the opportunity to take end-to-end ownership and responsibility across the full development lifecycle.

• Build from 0 to 1: You'll have the opportunity to both scale and automate existing services while also bringing new innovations to life. This is unique opportunity to help join a team where you'll be able to both build rapidly, and also contribute to product strategy and development! 

We are a highly collaborative team.

Who We're Looking For

The ideal candidate is a full-stack generalist, and has experience taking a product from 0-1 product. We're looking for someone who's entrepreneurial and willing to roll up their sleeves to get the work done, and passionate about our mission to build a platform that will intensely disrupt the healthcare industry.

• You are dangerous on the frontend of the stack.
• You are a highly skilled dev (React, TypeScript, Next.js, JavaScript, Tailwind).
• You have backend skills (SST, Lambda, Rust, mySQL, DynamoDB, Node).
• You can work independently and are comfortable owning entire projects and or large areas of the code base
• Strong experience in building paid products and services is preferred.
• You are a strong communicator - you are able to clearly articulate technical problems, constraints and timelines.
• You are comfortable working in a fast-paced, unstructured, startup environment.

highlightedJobListings.description:
### **About Numeric**

Numeric is building the modern accounting & finance platform. Companies today depend on Numeric's workflow and data platform to collaborate, monitor and analyze data, and share insights about their financials.

We believe an organization with up-to-date, accurate, rich financial data is empowered to move faster and smarter. Unfortunately, the tools and systems have not been keeping up. The complexity of work and granularity of data has ballooned, and old, slow software and simplistic tools only facilitate the manual work; they do little to solve the fundamental challenges of accounting and finance. As a product-focused company, we know that a great product and engineering team can build the tools to give our users superpowers. We work to free people from the manual and the tedious, and to bring delight to their work.

Numeric is backed by Founders Fund, Long Journey Ventures, and others as well as founders from Ramp, Segment, and more.

### **About the role**

Every engineer at Numeric is a product engineer. We believe the quality of a company's product is a direct reflection of its inclusion (or not) of engineers in every step of the product process. Ownership here means not only building, testing, and shipping your work, but also contributing to planning, scoping, and discovery. The role encompasses the entire loop of product iteration–observing and learning from users, designing solutions, building, and repeating until we've exceeded users' expectations.

Passionate builders improve through iteration, and learn by making mistakes. Our ideal candidate takes great pride in building and is excited by the ability to move fast. We place a great deal of emphasis on speed and ownership, and don't let anything get in your way.

### Projects we're working on

Here are a few projects you could get started with:

- Building the transaction monitoring engine to spot anomalies and help our users pre-empt costly errors

- Designing scheduling and automation of revenue and expenses

- Improving our one-of-a-kind flexible search & reporting platform for financial data

- Extending our real-time syncing integrations

- Launching new workflow automations on our generalized task system

### How we work

The engineering team here is a high-ownership, fast-paced, customer-focused group. We ship early & often. Deploys go out every day, and engineers ship & verify their own work. We keep things simple and do not incur operational cost or complexity until it's necessary. We stay grounded in our users and humble about what we don't know. We know that discovering the best solution is the result of an iterative, user-centric process. Finally, we move fast. With less than 2 years' time we're competing with existing players that have all been around for 10+ years.

### About you

- You thrive in a fast-paced and iterative environment. You are driven more by customer impact than technology.

- When building software, you can find [the 80/20 solution to a problem](https://www.notion.so/An-80-20-rule-for-product-development-83def9a3359149d780cb4245d498a42a?pvs=21).

- You're excited to build a new company, and to collaborate across all functions of the organization.

- You're allergic to premature optimization in all its forms; you focus on the larger goals at hand.

- The prospect of taking on incumbents as a small, high-performing team is an exciting challenge to you.

- You thrive when given more ownership and responsibility.

### Requirements

- Computer science or other technical degree

- 4+ years of experience in software engineering
